Definition.WordDefinition: Wichitas \Wich"i*tas\ (w[i^]ch"[i^]*t[add]z), prop. n. pl.; sing. {Wichita} (w[i^]ch"[i^]*t[add]). (Ethnol.) A tribe of Indians native of the region between the Arkansas and Red rivers. They are related to the Pawnees. See {Pawnees}. [1913 Webster]

Wichita n 1: a member of the Caddo people formerly living between Kansas and central Texas 2: the largest city in Kansas; located in southern Kansas on the Arkansas River 3: the Caddoan language spoken by the Wichita people
